tables.table_schema:
CREATE TABLE zoning_regulations (
  id INT PRIMARY KEY,
  land_use_category VARCHAR(255),
  zoning_code VARCHAR(50),
  maximum_building_height INT,
  setback_requirement INT
)

CREATE TABLE property_zoning (
    property_id INT PRIMARY KEY,
    zone_id INT,
    restriction_id INT,
    FOREIGN KEY (zone_id) REFERENCES land_use_zones(zone_id),
    FOREIGN KEY (restriction_id) REFERENCES zoning_restrictions(restriction_id)
);

CREATE TABLE zoning_map (
    ID SERIAL PRIMARY KEY,
    zone_id INTEGER NOT NULL,
    parcel_id INTEGER NOT NULL,
    FOREIGN KEY (zone_id) REFERENCES zoning_regulations(ID),
    FOREIGN KEY (parcel_id) REFERENCES parcels(ID)
);

CREATE TABLE zoning_regulations (
    id INT PRIMARY KEY,
    zone_name VARCHAR(100),
    land_use_type VARCHAR(100),
    height_limit DECIMAL(10,2),
    setback_distance DECIMAL(10,2)
);

CREATE TABLE building_permits (
    permit_id INT PRIMARY KEY,
    parcel_id INT,
    permit_date DATE,
    permit_type VARCHAR(100),
    FOREIGN KEY (parcel_id) REFERENCES parcel_information(parcel_id)
);

CREATE TABLE violation_records (
    violation_id INT PRIMARY KEY,
    permit_id INT,
    violation_date DATE,
    violation_description TEXT,
    FOREIGN KEY (permit_id) REFERENCES building_permits(permit_id)
);

CREATE TABLE inspector_records (
    inspector_id INT PRIMARY KEY,
    inspector_name VARCHAR(100),
    inspection_date DATE,
    violation_id INT,
    FOREIGN KEY (violation_id) REFERENCES violation_records(violation_id)
);
